The bulls sustained their hold on the equities sector of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), as more blue-chip stocks appreciated at price, causing market capitalisation to increase further by N4 billion.
   
Yesterday, the All-Share Index (ASI) increased by 8.41 absolute points, representing a growth of 0.03 per cent to close at 30,741.88 points.   Similarly, investors gained N4 billion as market capitalisation advanced to N16.068 trillion.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .